From: Hans Verkuil <hans.verkuil@cisco.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Jan 2018 03:24:53 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] media: v4l2-compat-ioctl32.c: don't copy back the result for certain errors
Git-commit: d83a8243aaefe62ace433e4384a4f077bed86acb
Patch-mainline: v4.16-rc1
References: CVE-2017-13166,bsc#1072865

Some ioctls need to copy back the result even if the ioctl returned
an error. However, don't do this for the error code -ENOTTY.
It makes no sense in that cases.

